## üóùÔ∏è Environment Variables

Configure your environment variables in a `.env.local` file or by using your system's variable management (such as Vercel, Docker, or others). A simplified example is shown below:


# .env.local

# App
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# NextAuth
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=
# Tip: You can generate with: openssl rand -base64 32

# Brevo (Email)
BREVO_API_KEY=
EMAIL_FROM=

# Supabase
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# Redis (Rate Limiting)
REDIS_URL=
REDIS_TOKEN=

# Cron
CRON_SECRET=